This we can configure from the Jenkins GUI for all the email receipents.

By Following the below Steps- 
a) Open Jenkins using the following URL: http://localhost:8080/ on any browser.
b) Click the ‘Manage Jenkins’ menu, where we need to select the ‘Manage Plugin’ option.
c) Search for the Email plugin.
d) Now, click the checkbox next to the ‘Email-ext Template Plugin’ option. Click the ‘Install without restart’ button.
e) Enter the SMTP server name under ‘Email Notification’. Click the ‘Advanced’ button and then click the checkbox next to the ‘Use SMTP Authentication’ option.
f) Check the email notification functionality by clicking the checkbox.

Plus whenever we will get the confirmation the job can be triggered from Jenkins by using "Mail Commander Plugin"
